亦ﾙ@3105d56981e2b0462bb54052a045c7bccf5b23890eba49f12b3b10e5ce89f4e6ﾚ裕itle: title: Nushell 0.43
Path: Nushell 0.43
Content:




Nushell, or Nu for short, is a new shell that takes a modern, structured approach to your commandline. It works seamlessly with the data from your filesystem, operating system, and a growing number of file formats to make it easy to build powerful commandline pipelines.
Today, we're releasing 0.43 of Nu. This release is a bugfix release of 0.42.
壷@d5ffc7d2457b6bebaf519fb4ad2f4ccec3228da05abc04b7d6baf60a6df7f789ﾚTitle: title: Nushell 0.43
Path: Where to get it
Content:
Nu 0.43 is available as 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/releases/tag/0.43.0] pre-built binaries
 or from 
[link: https://crates.io/crates/nu] crates.io
. If you have Rust installed you can install it using 
``cargo install nu``
.
If you want all the goodies, you can install 
``cargo install nu --features=extra``
.
As part of this release, we also publish a set of plugins you can install and use with Nu. To install, use 
``cargo install nu_plugin_<plugin name>``
.
壷@7b0033f6be39c822ae6c9dc43284bdeb423c14056d93002c35e20a81ddfb9714ﾚTitle: title: Nushell 0.43
Path: What's New
Content:
You can now learn about some of the upcoming changes in Nushell by reading the 
``tutor e-q``
 page. It will tell you about some of the new features and breaking changes, as well as link you to the full list of changes.
