壷@1f9836a0f79183ea5b8cb05a58fe4440cde273ba2a53356f30663f7108b2d27bﾚTitle: title: Nushell 0.43
Path: Engine-q progress
Content:
Engine-q is now nearly complete. Most of the commands have been ported, as has support for the 
``shells``
 feature, many reedline-related improvements, text encoding, and much more. It's now ready for early adopters to pick it up and use it as their shell, reporting any issues they find.
To try it out, you can 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/engine-q] build and run engine-q as a standalone application
. Also check out the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/engine-q/issues/459] list of configuration settings
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/engine-q/issues/522] list of breaking changes
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/engine-q/issues/735] the final checklist before engine-q merges into Nushell
.
We're hoping to merge engine-q into the main Nushell codebase after the the upcoming 0.44 release. We'll number this release 0.60 to show how much progress has been made by switching to the new engine. We've love to get your feedback on engine-q before it becomes the main Nushell, to help us fix any major issues before the merge happens. Let us know what you find!
You can check out a 
[link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c18l_HPsOxs] recent video about engine-q
 if you'd like to see it in action.
壷@fd35ca400164cd6d4b75e22217db769b2209558d3405d819cd50769ca5aff11aﾚﾟTitle: title: Nushell 0.43
Path: Looking forward
Content:
There are still 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/engine-q/issues/242] some commands left to port
 if you'd like to jump in and give porting a try. If you're interested, you can also help us by testing out engine-q itself as a shell and report your experiences with it. And of course, come join us on the 
[link: https://discord.gg/NtAbbGn] discord
. We'd be happy to show you around.
Thanks again for all your support.
